    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Honest little runaround that\u2019s ready for someone handy, a first project, or a cheap set of wheels. It\u2019s not a showpiece, but it\u2019s got plenty of life left for the right buyer and could make a great budget car, fixer-upper, or parts donor. Priced to be approachable and easy to justify if you\u2019re looking for something affordable without the usual song and dance. If you want a straightforward sale from a friendly seller, this is worth a look.",
      "price": 4900.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Turn-key project with solid enthusiast potential. This car shows its age cosmetically, but it still delivers the kind of analog, mechanical driving character that\u2019s getting harder to find. Engine starts, runs, and pulls with respectable urgency, transmission engages, and the chassis has the bones for a rewarding driver or weekend revival. Not a showroom car, but a great candidate for someone who appreciates honest used machinery and wants an affordable platform to sort, drive, and improve over time. Priced to move for the buyer who sees the upside.",
      "price": 6900.0,
